 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'kwalrath', 'comment_id': 337365756.0, 'datetime': '2017-10-17 20:47:10+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'I\'m mostly offline for the next 2 days, but if anyone wants to do the commit, here\'s my tweaked version:\r\n\r\nA programming language is nothing without its core libraries and tools. We call it _batteries included._ Dart\'s batteries have been powering very large apps for years now.\r\n\r\nIf we use quotation marks, it should be with the period inside ([unfortunately](https://developers.google.com/style/quotation-marks)): "batteries included."', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'wmleler', 'comment_id': 337379483.0, 'datetime': '2017-10-17 21:36:50+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': "I am on something of a personal crusade to get the punctuation inside the\nquotes rule changed. It all started years ago, when the editor on my first\nbook insisted that the punctuation had to be inside, even when it put a\nperiod inside what we were telling the user to type on their keyboard.\nStupid. My new rule is that if the thing in quotes is not a complete\nsentence, then there is no need to move any punctuation inside the trailing\nquote. It also better handles cases like when the thing inside quotes is a\nquestion, but what's outside is not (and vice-versa).\n\nI've been using the new rule on my blog. It has been going for 9 years and\nnobody has complained yet.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'kwalrath', 'comment_id': 337384506.0, 'datetime': '2017-10-17 21:54:29+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "I completely agree, Wm, and in my personal writing I follow that rule. But I also believe that we should follow the style guide whenever possible. If you'd like to change the style guide, I can connect you with the powers that be.\r\n\r\n(That said, I usually end up writing around the problem.)", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
